                <h2>Core Mechanic: Shadowblight</h2>
                <p>The Shadowblight passive triggers after <strong>8 Shadow damage instances</strong> hit an enemy within a 2-second window. When it procs, it deals a massive burst of Shadow damage based on your <strong>weapon damage multiplied by your total Shadow damage %</strong>.</p>
                <p>The key insight is that Shadowblight counts <strong>hits per second</strong>, not big individual hits. Every Blight tick, every Corpse Explosion hit, every Soulrift pulse -- they all count as separate Shadow instances. This means Attack Speed, multi-hit skills, and overlapping AoE are far more valuable than raw per-hit damage.</p>
                <p>The <strong>Blighted Aspect</strong> amplifies this further by granting a <strong>70% damage multiplier per Shadowblight proc</strong>, which stacks in dense packs where you are triggering procs on multiple enemies simultaneously.</p>

