            <div class="section">
                <h2>Paragon Board Order</h2>
                <p>Attach boards in this order. Route through nodes that give Intelligence, Shadow damage, and damage reduction. Socket the listed Glyph in each board's Glyph socket once it reaches level 15 for the bonus radius.</p>

                <div class="paragon-board">
                    <div class="paragon-board-header">
                        <span class="paragon-board-name">1. Starting Board</span>
                        <span class="paragon-board-order">Board 1</span>
                    </div>
                    <p style="color: #c0c0c0; margin: 0;">Glyph: <span class="glyph-name">Eliminator</span></p>
                    <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 8px;">Eliminator increases damage to injured and crowd-controlled enemies. Since Corpse Tendrils stuns everything and Decrepify slows, this glyph has near-100% uptime. Route toward the Rare nodes that grant damage to Vulnerable enemies.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="paragon-board">
                    <div class="paragon-board-header">
                        <span class="paragon-board-name">2. Scent of Death</span>
                        <span class="paragon-board-order">Board 2</span>
                    </div>
                    <p style="color: #c0c0c0; margin: 0;">Glyph: <span class="glyph-name">Sacrificial</span></p>
                    <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 8px;">Sacrificial grants bonus damage per sacrificed minion type. With all three types sacrificed, this is one of the strongest glyphs for this build. The Scent of Death board has nodes that boost damage after consuming corpses, synergizing with your constant Corpse Explosion usage.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="paragon-board">
                    <div class="paragon-board-header">
                        <span class="paragon-board-name">3. Blood Begets Blood</span>
                        <span class="paragon-board-order">Board 3</span>
                    </div>
                    <p style="color: #c0c0c0; margin: 0;">Glyph: <span class="glyph-name">Essence</span></p>
                    <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 8px;">Essence glyph increases damage based on your current Essence amount. With Soulrift regenerating Essence constantly, you maintain high Essence for the damage bonus. This board provides additional life and damage nodes that shore up survivability in the mid-game Paragon range.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="paragon-board">
                    <div class="paragon-board-header">
                        <span class="paragon-board-name">4. Wither</span>
                        <span class="paragon-board-order">Board 4</span>
                    </div>
                    <p style="color: #c0c0c0; margin: 0;">Glyph: <span class="glyph-name">Gravekeeper</span></p>
                    <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 8px;">Gravekeeper grants bonus damage after consuming a corpse. Since you consume corpses every few seconds (Corpse Explosion, Corpse Tendrils), this buff is permanently active. The Wither board has Legendary node bonuses to Shadow DoT damage that directly scale Blight pools and Shadowblight procs.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="paragon-board">
                    <div class="paragon-board-header">
                        <span class="paragon-board-name">5. Frailty</span>
