        <div id="gameplay" class="tab-content">

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Combat Rotation</h2>
                <p>The rotation is straightforward once you internalize the corpse economy. Your goal is to generate corpses, group enemies, and saturate them with Shadow hits to trigger Shadowblight procs as fast as possible.</p>

                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Soulrift on Cooldown</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Cast Soulrift whenever it is available. It applies Vulnerable to all enemies in range, regenerates your Essence, provides DR, and generates Shadow ticks that count toward Shadowblight stacking. This is your opener for every pack and your sustain tool during extended fights.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Reap Once for Corpse</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Use Reap on any enemy to generate an initial corpse. Enhanced Reap guarantees a corpse on hit. This also activates Acolyte's Reap DR and attack speed buffs. One swing is enough -- do not spam Reap.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Corpse Tendrils to Pull + CC</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Consume a corpse with Corpse Tendrils to pull all nearby enemies into a tight group and stun them. Plagued Corpse Tendrils applies Vulnerable (stacking with Soulrift). Aspect of Grasping Veins grants Crit Chance against the pulled enemies. This is your setup step -- everything that follows hits harder because of it.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Spam Corpse Explosion</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">With enemies grouped and Vulnerable, spam Corpse Explosion on every available corpse. Blighted Corpse Explosion converts all damage to Shadow and leaves Shadow pools. Each explosion counts as multiple Shadow hits across all enemies in range, rapidly stacking Shadowblight. In dense packs, 2-3 explosions trigger the first proc.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Weave Blight Between Explosions</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Cast Blight between Corpse Explosions to drop Shadow pools that tick continuously. Paranormal Blight makes enemies standing in pools take increased Shadow damage. The persistent ticks help maintain Shadowblight stacks on enemies that survive the initial burst and contribute to subsequent procs.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Reap Every 3-4 Seconds</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">Refresh Acolyte's Reap DR and attack speed buff by swinging Reap every 3-4 seconds. This also generates additional corpses for sustaining Corpse Explosion chains. Do not let the buffs fall off -- the DR is significant for survivability.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <div>
                            <p><strong style="color: #d4af37;">Decrepify -- Auto-Applied</strong></p>
                            <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem;">With Aspect of the Cursed Aura, Decrepify automatically applies to all nearby enemies. You do not need to cast it manually. Enemies are constantly slowed, deal reduced damage, and trigger Abhorrent Decrepify CDR when they die. Aspect of the Damned ensures they take bonus Shadow damage.</p>
                        </div>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Tips & Advanced Play</h2>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Corpse Economy is Everything</strong>
                    <p>Your build does nothing without corpses. Hewed Flesh passive + Reap ensures you always have corpses, but in long boss fights you may run dry. Save at least 1 corpse for Corpse Tendrils CC at all times -- do not blow every corpse on Explosions.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Stack Hits, Not Big Hits</strong>
                    <p>Shadowblight counts instances, not damage. Three weak Blight ticks + two Corpse Explosions + three Soulrift pulses = 8 stacks = proc. Prioritize overlapping AoE and Attack Speed over raw per-hit damage when gearing.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Positioning for Maximum Overlap</strong>
                    <p>Stand near your Blight pools and Corpse Tendrils so that Cursed Aura (Decrepify auto-apply) hits the same enemies being damaged by your Shadow ticks. The more debuffs stacked on a target when Shadowblight procs, the higher the burst.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Boss Strategy</strong>
                    <p>Against mobile bosses, use Corpse Tendrils to root them in your Blight pools. Cast Soulrift on top of the boss for guaranteed Vulnerable. Without grouped adds, Shadowblight procs are slower -- focus on maintaining Blight uptime and weaving Reap for corpse generation. Blood Moon Breeches Crit Damage helps make each proc count.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Essence Management</strong>
                    <p>Blight costs Essence. Soulrift regenerates it. If Soulrift is on cooldown and you are low, fall back to Reap (free) and Corpse Explosion (free, uses corpses not Essence) until Soulrift comes back. Abhorrent Decrepify CDR helps get Soulrift back faster.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Evade = Unstoppable</strong>
                    <p>With Aspect of Metamorphosis on boots, your Evade grants Unstoppable. Save it for Crowd Control emergencies, not for repositioning. In Pit content, getting frozen or stunned without Unstoppable available is often lethal.</p>
                </div>
